Topics
● JSX
JSX formally is a JavaScript extension that allows creation of DOM trees using an HTML/XML-like syntax.

● React.createElement vs JSX
React.createElement is used to create React element.
JSX is JavaScript extension that allows creation of DOM trees using an HTML/XML-like syntax.

● Benefits of JSX
With JSX, you can write large pieces of code in a more organized and simplified manner. 

● Behind the Scenes of JSX

● Babel & parcel role in JSX
Parcel is manager of Babel and Bable is compiler of JS which transpiles code that JS engine can understand

● Components
Class Based Components
Functional Components

● Functional Components is a function which returns some JSX code

○ Composing Components is calling 1 function inside the another

Assignment
● What is JSX?
JSX formally is a JavaScript extension that allows creation of DOM trees using an HTML/XML-like syntax.

● Superpowers of JSX

● Role of type attribute in script tag? What options can I use there?
The type attribute specifies the type of the script.
The type attribute identifies the content between the <script> and </script> tags.



● {TitleComponent} vs {<TitleComponent/>} vs
{<TitleComponent></TitleComponent>} in JSX
All three are same

